{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code Chapter 10.40 VISION OBSTRUCTIONS AT INTERSECTIONS 10.40.010 Obstructions at intersections prohibited. 10.40.020 Exceptions. 10.40.030 Authority of traffic engineer. 10.40.040 Responsibility of owner. 10.40.050 Appeal procedure. 10.40.060 Nuisance. 10.40.070 Cost of abatement a charge against the city\u2014Collection of costs, unpaid costs of lien. 10.40.080 Alternate method of collection\u2014Addition to tax bill of amount of costs\u2014Procedure.", "num": "10.40", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40", "title": "Chapter 10.40 VISION OBSTRUCTIONS AT INTERSECTIONS", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.010 Obstructions at intersections prohibited. Notwithstanding any other provisions of law to the contrary, no fence, hedge, shrub, wall, retaining wall, earthen bank, or other landscaping or screening which exceeds a height of three feet above the street-pavement grade shall be allowed along the property lines or their projection, which is equal to the sum of the building setbacks on each of the two intersecting streets, existing or legal, whichever is less, or, within the area subtended. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 220, 1992.) Cross References Section 10.48.020", "num": "10.40.010", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.010", "title": "10.40.010 Obstructions at intersections prohibited.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.020 Exceptions. The foregoing provisions shall not apply to a permanent building or to trees which are trimmed to eliminate foliage for a distance of eight feet above the street-pavement grade. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 221, 1992.)", "num": "10.40.020", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.020", "title": "10.40.020 Exceptions.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.030 Authority of traffic engineer. The traffic engineer of the city, upon ascertaining that a violation of the above provisions exists, shall give written notice of the violation to the owner of the property involved. Such notice shall be given in the same manner and with the same effect as provided in Section 1013 of the California Code of Civil Procedure . (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 222, 1992.)", "num": "10.40.030", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.030", "title": "10.40.030 Authority of traffic engineer.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.040 Responsibility of owner. The property owner to whom the notice is given shall, within twenty days after the giving of notice by the Traffic Engineer, as provided in the preceding section, do whatever is necessary on his or her property to eliminate the violation of the provisions of this chapter . (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 223, 1992.)", "num": "10.40.040", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.040", "title": "10.40.040 Responsibility of owner.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.050 Appeal procedure. The property owner to whom notice has been given, as hereinabove provided, may, within ten days after the giving of such notice, file with the traffic engineer a written notice of appeal. The city public safety committee shall have the power, in exceptional cases, where it is impractical or physically impossible to comply with the strict letter of this chapter , and in order to provide for reasonable interpretations thereof, to modify the requirements of this chapter , in such a manner that the public welfare is secured, and substantial justice done, nearly in accord with the intent and purpose of this chapter . The determination and decision of the committee shall be final and conclusive. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 224, 1992.)", "num": "10.40.050", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.050", "title": "10.40.050 Appeal procedure.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.060 Nuisance. A condition which is in violation of the provisions of this chapter is hereby declared to be a public nuisance. The city is authorized to abate such nuisance by entering onto the property and removing the condition. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 225, 1992.)", "num": "10.40.060", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.060", "title": "10.40.060 Nuisance.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.070 Cost of abatement a charge against the city\u2014Collection of costs, unpaid costs of lien. (A) Costs incurred by the city in the abatement of a condition which is in violation of the provisions of this chapter shall be a proper charge against the city treasury and paid therefrom. The traffic engineer shall give the owner of the property upon which the condition exists a written notice itemizing the expense of such abatement and requesting payment. If the amount of such costs is not paid to the traffic engineer within five days after giving such notice, he shall record in the office of the recorder of Napa County, California, a certificate substantially in the following form: \"Notice of Lien\" \"Pursuant to authority vested in me by the American Canyon Traffic Code, I did on the day of ____, 20____, cause to be abated, at the owner's expense, in the amount of $ _____, a condition upon the real property hereinafter described. Said amount, nor any part, has not been paid. The City of American Canyon does hereby claim a lien upon said real property in said amount, which amount shall remain a lien upon said real property until paid in full, together with interest at the rate of 7% per annum from the date of recordation of this lien in the office of the Recorder of Napa County, California. The real property upon which lien is claimed is that certain parcel of land in the City of American Canyon, County of Napa, State of California, described as follows: (Insert property description) Dated: ______, 20____. __________________________ American Canyon Traffic Engineer (B) Costs incurred in such abatement shall remain a lien upon the property described in the lien notice until paid in full, plus accrued interest at the rate of seven percent per annum from the date of recordation. The statute of limitations shall not run against the city's right to enforce payment of such lien. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 226, 1992.)", "num": "10.40.070", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.070", "title": "10.40.070 Cost of abatement a charge against the city\u2014Collection of costs, unpaid costs of lien.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.080", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.40.080 Alternate method of collection\u2014Addition to tax bill of amount of costs\u2014Procedure. (A) As an alternative method of collection of the amount of the lien, the traffic engineer may record the notice of lien, as hereinabove provided, and may thereafter transmit it, or a facsimile, to the county auditor, who shall thereupon enter that amount on the county assessment book opposite the description of the particular lot or parcel of land; and the amount shall be collected together with all other taxes levied against the property. (B) The assessment shall be subject to the same penalties and interest and to the same procedure under foreclosure and sale in case of delinquency as is provided for all other municipal and county taxes against the property; and all laws applicable to the levy, collection and enforcement to such special assessment. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 227, 1992.) Cross References Section 10.48.020", "num": "10.40.080", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.40|10.40.080", "title": "10.40.080 Alternate method of collection\u2014Addition to tax bill of amount of costs\u2014Procedure.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.40.080"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code Chapter 10.44 BICYCLES 10.44.010 Operation of bicycles on roadways and bicycle routes. 10.44.020 Bicycle equipment. 10.44.030 Parking bicycles. 10.44.040 Licensing of bicycles. 10.44.050 Licensing agency. 10.44.060 Registration forms. 10.44.070 Licensing and registration forms. 10.44.080 Licensing and registration fees. 10.44.090 Disposition of fees. 10.44.100 Renewal of expired licenses. 10.44.110 Transfers of ownership. 10.44.120 Notification of change of address. 10.44.130 Tampering with registration certificates, bicycle licenses and serial numbers. 10.44.140 Bicycles in violation of laws. 10.44.150 Rental agencies. 10.44.160 Violations. 10.44.170 Fines.", "num": "10.44", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44", "title": "Chapter 10.44 BICYCLES", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.010 Operation of bicycles on roadways and bicycle routes. (A) No person operating a bicycle upon a highway shall ride other than upon or astride a permanent and regular seat attached thereto. (B) No operator shall allow a person riding as a passenger on a bicycle, and no person shall ride as a passenger on a bicycle, upon a highway other than upon or astride a separate seat attached thereto. If the passenger is a child, the seat shall have adequate provisions for retaining the child in place and for protecting the child from the moving parts of the bicycle. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 121, 1992.) Cross References Section 10.48.020", "num": "10.44.010", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.010", "title": "10.44.010 Operation of bicycles on roadways and bicycle routes.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.020 Bicycle equipment. (A) All bicycles licensed pursuant to this chapter shall conform to all the equipment requirements specified by the Vehicle Code and this code. (B) No person shall operate upon a highway a bicycle which is of such a size as to prevent the operator from stopping the bicycle, supporting it in an upright position with at least one foot on the highway surface, and restarting it in a safe manner. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 122, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.020", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.020", "title": "10.44.020 Bicycle equipment.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.030 Parking bicycles. (A) No person shall park a bicycle upon a street or against a building in such a manner as to obstruct pedestrian, bicycle, or motor vehicular traffic. (B) No person shall leave a bicycle lying on its side on any sidewalk or park a bicycle on a sidewalk in a position that does not leave an adequate path for pedestrian traffic. (C) Notwithstanding subsections A and B of this section , no person shall park a bicycle at any location which has been posted with signs prohibiting such parking. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 123, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.030", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.030", "title": "10.44.030 Parking bicycles.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.040 Licensing of bicycles. (A) No city resident shall ride, move, haul, or leave standing or allow to be ridden, moved, hauled, or left standing, any bicycle on any road, street, highway, or other public property unless such bicycle is licensed in accordance with this chapter . (B) This section shall not apply to bicycle manufacturers or bicycle dealers transporting bicycles in the normal course of business.", "num": "10.44.040", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.040", "title": "10.44.040 Licensing of bicycles.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.050 Licensing agency. The American Canyon fire protection district, a subsidiary district of the city, shall be responsible for carrying out the provisions of this chapter and is authorized and directed to register and license bicycles upon a written application for a license and the payment of the required fee. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 125, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.050", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.050", "title": "10.44.050 Licensing agency.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.060 Registration forms. The registration form shall contain the following: (A) The name and address of the registered owner, (B) The make, type and model of the bicycle, (C) The serial number of the bicycle, (D) The license number of the bicycle, (E) The original date of sale, (F) A place for the name and address of a new registered owner, (G) A place for the signature of the registered owner, (H) A place for the signature of the registered owner releasing his interest, (I) A place for the signature of the new registered owner, and (J) A place for the name of the licensing agency. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 126, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.060", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.060", "title": "10.44.060 Registration forms.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.070 Licensing and registration forms. (A) Bicycle licenses and registration forms shall be supplied to the licensing agency by the city. (B) The license shall be permanently affixed to the bicycle by the licensing agency and the registration form completed at the time of the registration or sale, whichever occurs first. (C) Records shall be maintained by each licensing agency during the period of validity of the license. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 127, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.070", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.070", "title": "10.44.070 Licensing and registration forms.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.080", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.080 Licensing and registration fees. Upon an application for registration and licensing, the fee required pursuant to the provisions of this chapter shall be five dollars for a five-year license. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 128, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.080", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.080", "title": "10.44.080 Licensing and registration fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.080"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.090", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.090 Disposition of fees. (A) For each bicycle registered and licensed by a bicycle dealer a fee of fifty cents out of the license fee received may be retained by the bicycle dealer for his services. (B) Revenues from the registration, replacement, and renewal of the license shall be paid to the director of finance monthly, and shall be retained by the city in a separate account, and shall be used for the support of the bicycle licensing and registration programs, and to improve bicycle safety programs, and to establish bicycle facilities, including bicycle paths and lanes, within the incorporated city limits. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 129, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.090", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.090", "title": "10.44.090 Disposition of fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.090"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.100", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.100 Renewal of expired licenses. The owner of a bicycle may have an expired bicycle license renewed upon the presentation of the bicycle, the last issued registration form or its copy, and the payment of the fee prescribed. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 130, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.100", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.100", "title": "10.44.100 Renewal of expired licenses.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.100"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.110", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.110 Transfers of ownership. (A) Whenever the owner of the bicycle licensed pursuant to this chapter sells or otherwise disposes of a bicycle, he shall, within ten days, notify the licensing agency of such disposition. (B) Any person who purchases or otherwise acquires the possession of a bicycle shall, within ten days of taking such possession, apply for the transfer of the license for such bicycle to his name. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 131, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.110", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.110", "title": "10.44.110 Transfers of ownership.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.110"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.120", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.120 Notification of change of address. Whenever the owner of a registered bicycle licensed pursuant to this chapter changes his address, he shall, within ten days, notify the licensing agency of the old and new address. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 132, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.120", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.120", "title": "10.44.120 Notification of change of address.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.120"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.130", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.130 Tampering with registration certificates, bicycle licenses and serial numbers. (A) It shall be unlawful for any person to tamper with, destroy, mutilate, or alter any registration certificate issued pursuant to the provisions of this chapter . (B) It shall be unlawful for any person to remove, destroy, mutilate, or in any way alter or tamper with any bicycle license issued pursuant to the provisions of this chapter . (C) It shall be unlawful for any person to remove, alter, or mutilate the serial number of any bicycle frame licensed pursuant to the provisions of this chapter . (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 133, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.130", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.130", "title": "10.44.130 Tampering with registration certificates, bicycle licenses and serial numbers.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.130"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.140", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.140 Bicycles in violation of laws. The licensing agency shall have the right to impound and retain the possession of any bicycle on which the manufacturer's identification numbers have been altered, defaced, removed or destroyed. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 134, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.140", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.140", "title": "10.44.140 Bicycles in violation of laws.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.140"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.150", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.150 Rental agencies. A rental agency operating within the city shall not rent or offer any bicycle for rent unless such bicycle is licensed as provided in this chapter . (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 135, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.150", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.150", "title": "10.44.150 Rental agencies.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.150"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.160", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 10.44.160 Violations. Any violation of the provisions of this chapter shall be an infraction. (Ord. 92-19 \u00a7 136, 1992.)", "num": "10.44.160", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|10|10.44|10.44.160", "title": "10.44.160 Violations.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/10.44.160"}
