{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code Chapter 14.04 WASTEWATER RATES AND CHARGES 14.04.005 Definitions. 14.04.010 Wastewater monthly service charge\u2014Purpose. 14.04.020 Wastewater service charges \u2013 Residential service 14.04.030 Wastewater service charge\u2014Mobile home residential service 14.04.040 Wastewater service charge\u2014Multifamily 14.04.050 Wastewater service charges\u2014Nonresidential, normal strength 14.04.060 Wastewater service charges\u2014Nonresidential, high strength. 14.04.070 Wastewater service charges\u2014adopted by resolution. 14.04.080 Wastewater connection charge\u2014Industrial service. 14.04.090 Temporary wastewater connection fees. 14.04.100 Adjustments to wastewater connection fees. 14.04.110 Reclaimed water mains. 14.04.120 Revenue for repayment of loan\u2014Wastewater capital reserve fund.", "num": "14.04", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04", "title": "Chapter 14.04 WASTEWATER RATES AND CHARGES", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.005", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.005 Definitions. For purposes of this chapter , the definitions in Sections 13.06.010 of the Municipal Code shall be construed as applicable to this chapter except as set forth in this section : \"High strength, nonresidential customer\" includes all customers whose discharge exceeds the levels of biochemical oxygen demand (BOD) or total suspended solids (TSS) set forth in the \"normal strength, nonresidential customer\" definition in this section . \"Meter factor\" means the ratio applied to meter readings to determine the billable flow for nonresidential users. For domestic water meters, the factor shall equal 1.00; for sewer meters the flow shall equal 1.11. \"Multifamily residential\" includes any premises that is residential in nature and consists of more than one dwelling unit served by a single metered water connection. Such master-metered customers shall be charged as set forth in this chapter . Temporary residential premises (e.g., hotels) are treated as a commercial use. \"Normal strength, nonresidential customer\" includes all customers whose discharge conforms to \"normal strength, nonresidential wastewater\" but not included as residential customers in Sections 14.04.010 and 14.04.020 . In lieu of separate analysis or adopted tables per Section 14.04.040 , these customers shall generally include churches, public schools, private schools, commercial facilities, industrial facilities, government uses, and office buildings. The city reserves the right to assign any customer to high strength, nonresidential status, based on that customer's actual BOD or TSS. \"Normal strength, nonresidential wastewater\" means all wastewater discharged to the city wastewater collection system with a BOD of no more than two hundred thirty six milligrams per liter or a TSS of no more than two hundred thirty-six milligrams per liter. (Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007.) Cross References Section 14.04.060(A) Section 14.06.020(D)", "num": "14.04.005", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.005", "title": "14.04.005 Definitions.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.005"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.010 Wastewater monthly service charge\u2014Purpose. (A) It shall be city policy to at all times collect wastewater rates and charges that meet but do not exceed the cost of service of the wastewater enterprise. (B) It shall be city policy to set wastewater rates and charges that are fair and equitable to all customer classes and recover each customer's share of the total cost of service in proportion to their use of the system. (C) It shall be city policy to have a wastewater rate study performed, by a qualified independent rate consultant, every three to five years, to ensure that wastewater rates charges, and connection fees are set to an appropriate level. Rate studies will be based on AWWA rate setting principles and shall recommend rates that meet the cost of service of the wastewater enterprise. (D) The city may exercise its discretion consistent with Hansen v. City of San Buenaventura, 42 Cal.3d 1172 (1986) to enact a rate for property owners outside the city which is forty percent greater than the rate for property owners within the city. (Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007.) Cross References Section 14.04.005", "num": "14.04.010", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.010", "title": "14.04.010 Wastewater monthly service charge\u2014Purpose.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.020 Wastewater service charges \u2013 Residential service (A) As of the effective date of the ordinance, or January 1, 2025, whichever comes later, each residential customer shall pay for wastewater services per dwelling unit per month according to the schedule outlined below: 01/01/25 01/01/26 01/01/27 01/01/28 01/01/29 Single Family Residential $74.94 $89.93 $100.72 $112.81 $112.81 Multi-Family Residential $48.70 $58.44 $65.45 $73.31 $73.31 (B) Effective January 1, 2030, and on every January 1st thereafter, wastewater service charges will be adjusted by the percent change in the Bay Area Consumer Price Index over the previous calendar year, or by three percent, whichever is less. ( Ord. No. 2024-05 Section 6 ; Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007; Ord. 2011-06 \u00a7 1, 2011.) Cross References Section 14.04.005 Section 14.04.030(A) Section 14.04.040(A)", "num": "14.04.020", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.020", "title": "14.04.020 Wastewater service charges \u2013 Residential service", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.030 Wastewater service charge\u2014Mobile home residential service (A) Each mobile home customer with an individual metered account shall be considered a Multi-Family Residential Customer and pay for wastewater services according to the schedule set forth in ACMC 14.040.020 . ( Ord. No. 2024-05 Section 7 ; Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007; Ord. 2011-06 \u00a7 2, 2011.)", "num": "14.04.030", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.030", "title": "14.04.030 Wastewater service charge\u2014Mobile home residential service", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.040 Wastewater service charge\u2014Multifamily (A) Each multi-family residential customer shall pay for wastewater services according to the schedule set forth in ACMC 14.040.020 . ( Ord. No. 2024-05 Section 8 ; Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007; Ord. 2011-06 \u00a7 3, 2011.) Cross References Section 14.04.005", "num": "14.04.040", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.040", "title": "14.04.040 Wastewater service charge\u2014Multifamily", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.050 Wastewater service charges\u2014Nonresidential, normal strength (A) As of the effective date of the ordinance, or January 1, 2025, whichever comes later, each normal strength, nonresidential customer shall pay both a monthly service charge and a volumetric charge for wastewater services according to the schedule outlined below: 01/01/25 01/01/26 01/01/27 01/01/28 01/01/29 Monthly Service Charge $115.21 $138.25 $154.84 $173.42 $173.42 Volumetric Rate ($/HCF) $1.92 $2.31 $2.58 $2.89 $2.89 The volumetric charge shall be equal to the volumetric rate established by schedule above ($/HCF) multiplied by the quantity of water delivered to the customer pursuant to ACMC 13.04 . (B) Effective January 1, 2030, and on every January 1st thereafter, wastewater service charges will be adjusted by the percent change in the Bay Area Consumer Price Index over the previous calendar year, or by three percent, whichever is less. ( Ord. No. 2024-05 Section 9 ; Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007; Ord. 2011-06 \u00a7 4, 2011.) Cross References Section 14.06.030(A)", "num": "14.04.050", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.050", "title": "14.04.050 Wastewater service charges\u2014Nonresidential, normal strength", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.060 Wastewater service charges\u2014Nonresidential, high strength. (A) Each high strength, nonresidential customer as defined in Section 14.04.005 shall pay the greater of the following fixed monthly fees or a fee calculated according to the following formula. 1-Jan-08 1-Jan-09 1-Jan-10 High strength\u2014nonresidential (fixed) $36.79 $40.29 $44.11 Or On January 1, 2008: Charge = Water Unit X Meter Factor [$1.47+ ($.91 x BOD in mg/l) + ($.91 x TSS in mg/l) ] 236 238 On January 1, 2009: Charge = Water Unit X Meter Factor [$1.62+ ($.99 x BOD in mg/l) + ($.99 x TSS in mg/l) ] 236 238 On January 1, 2010: Charge = Water Unit X Meter Factor [ $1.78+ ($1.08 x BOD in mg/l) + ($1.08 x TSS in mg/l) ] 236 238 (B) For purposes of determining BOD and TSS in the above formulae, city staff is authorized to require analysis of the user's flow in accordance with Title 14 of this code. For installations that use less than two thousand gallons per day of domestic water, city staff may use published tables of BOD and TSS that are approved by the State Water Resources Control Board for use in determining BOD and TSS in the above formulae. (C) Effective January 1, 2012, and on every January 1st thereafter, wastewater service charges will be adjusted by the percent change in the Bay Area Consumer Price Index over the previous calendar year, or by three percent, whichever is less. (Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007; Ord. 2011-06 \u00a7 5, 2011.)", "num": "14.04.060", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.060", "title": "14.04.060 Wastewater service charges\u2014Nonresidential, high strength.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.070 Wastewater service charges\u2014adopted by resolution. The city council declares its intent to make any future changes in the wastewater rates established in this chapter by setting forth the changes in a resolution duly adopted, and the adoption of such a resolution shall have the same force and effect as though the changes had been made by the adoption of an ordinance. (Ord. 2007-14 \u00a7 3, 2007.) Cross References Section 14.04.100(B)", "num": "14.04.070", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.070", "title": "14.04.070 Wastewater service charges\u2014adopted by resolution.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.080", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.080 Wastewater connection charge\u2014Industrial service. (A) At the time of submission of application for building permit for an industrial building connection to the city wastewater collection system, an applicant shall pay a sanitary sewer connection charge for industrial uses in accordance with the following formula: Connection Fee = $35.11 x (flow (in gpd) x (0.85 + (.09 x BOD (in mg/l) \u00f7 236) + (0.6 x TSS (in mg/l) \u00f7 238))) The terms BOD and TSS are as 4.08.010 and are expressed in milligrams per liter (mg/l). Values of BOD and TSS for a particular project shall be subject to approval by the city engineer. The charges shall be subject to adjustment in accordance with Section 14.04.100 . (B) If, after connection to city wastewater facilities and review of the discharger's flow data or water use data for any given period, it is determined by the city engineer that the discharger has increased flow, BOD, or TSS levels above those requested at the time of application, then the applicant shall be charged for the increased flow, BOD, or TSS at the then applicable rate as provided in the city's wastewater connection fee ordinance and as determined by the city engineer. The applicant and/or discharger shall pay the revised connection fee within sixty days of demand by the city; failure to pay the charges within the specified time may result in termination of water and sewer service by the city to the extent allowed by existing law. (Ord. 2001-03 \u00a7 5, 2001; Ord. 2004-06 \u00a7 3, 2004.) Cross References Section 14.04.100(B)", "num": "14.04.080", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.080", "title": "14.04.080 Wastewater connection charge\u2014Industrial service.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.080"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.090", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.090 Temporary wastewater connection fees. The city council may adopt by resolution, temporary wastewater connection fees based on a fording by the city council that a particular use is temporary and does not conform to the typical use categories of residential, commercial or industrial. In such cases the temporary wastewater connection fee shall be charged for each unit of seven hundred forty-eight gallons of wastewater flow based on the following formula: Temporary Connection Fee = $4.20/unit of wastewater x (0.85 + (.09 x BOD (in mg/l) \u00f7 236) + (0.6 x TSS (in mg/l) \u00f7 238)) The city manager or city manager's designee may be delegated responsibility for billing and monitoring temporary connection fees in accordance with this section . (Ord. 2001-03 \u00a7 6, 2001; Ord. 2004-06 \u00a7 4, 2004.)", "num": "14.04.090", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.090", "title": "14.04.090 Temporary wastewater connection fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.090"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.100", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.100 Adjustments to wastewater connection fees. (A) The city at its sole discretion may adopt revised wastewater connection fees based on the pro-commit participation by the general fund of the city proportionate effects of inflation or changes to the cost of living. For purposes of calculation, the Engineering News Record 20-City Construction Cost Index shall be used for adjusting said fees. Said adjustments in accordance with this section may be approved by a resolution of the city council. (B) At the sole discretion of the city council applicants may be charged either the industrial wastewater service connection fee in accordance with Section 14.04.080(A) and (B), or Section 14.04.070 , connection fees, commercial wastewater service connection fee. (C) The city council, at its sole discretion, may commit participation by the general fund of the city for fifty percent of the connection fee in an amount not to exceed ten thousand dollars to be applied to wastewater connection fees for a qualifying nonprofit or charitable organization in the city. (Ord. 2001-03 \u00a7 7, 2001; Ord. 2004-06 \u00a7 5, 2004.) Cross References Section 14.04.080", "num": "14.04.100", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.100", "title": "14.04.100 Adjustments to wastewater connection fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.100"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.110", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.110 Reclaimed water mains. The city council may adopt by resolution a plan of reclaimed water mains to serve future growth of the city. New development which fronts such reclaimed water mains may be required to install such mains at no cost to the city. (Ord. 2001-03 \u00a7 8, 2001.)", "num": "14.04.110", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.110", "title": "14.04.110 Reclaimed water mains.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.110"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.120", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.04.120 Revenue for repayment of loan\u2014Wastewater capital reserve fund. (A) The city dedicates the following sources of revenue to repayment of any and all State Revolving Fund loans on Project No. C-06-4666-110, the water treatment and reclamation project: waste user charges, wastewater connection fees and connection fees, where appropriate. This dedicated source of revenue shall remain in effect until any such loan (or loans) is fully discharged, unless modification or change of such dedication is approved in writing by the State Water Resources Control Board. (B) A wastewater capital reserve fund is established. Deposits to the fund shall be made annually at a rate set by resolution by city council, not to exceed seventy-five thousand dollars per year but at least one-half percent of the loan amount for the wastewater treatment plant project. Such funds shall be maintained in accordance with \"The Policy for Implementation State Revolving Fund for Construction of Waste Water Treatment Facilities,\" as adopted by the state of California Water Resources Control Board. (Ord. 99-04, 1999; Ord. 2001-03 \u00a7 2, 2001.)", "num": "14.04.120", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.04|14.04.120", "title": "14.04.120 Revenue for repayment of loan\u2014Wastewater capital reserve fund.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.04.120"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code Chapter 14.06 WASTEWATER CAPACITY FEE 14.06.010 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014Purpose. 14.06.020 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014All normal strength connections. 14.06.030 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014High strength or industrial. 14.06.040 Wastewater use substantially altered\u2014Additional wastewater capacity fee. 14.06.050 Temporary wastewater connection fees. 14.06.060 Adjustments to wastewater connection fees. 14.06.070 Reclaimed water mains. 14.06.080 Revenue for repayment of loan\u2014Wastewater capital reserve fund.", "num": "14.06", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06", "title": "Chapter 14.06 WASTEWATER CAPACITY FEE", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.06.010 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014Purpose. The purpose of a wastewater capacity fee or wastewater connection fee is to allow the city to recover the costs associated with providing a new connection to the system with capacity in the wastewater system. The fee is set to recover the costs of all existing infrastructure, provided by existing customers for the benefit of the new connection, as well as all future capital projects required to provide that new connection with sufficient wastewater collection, treatment, and disposal capacity in the system. (Ord. 2007-12 \u00a7 1, 2007.)", "num": "14.06.010", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06|14.06.010", "title": "14.06.010 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014Purpose.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.06.020 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014All normal strength connections. (A) At the time of submission of application for building permit for connection to the city wastewater collection system, an applicant shall pay a wastewater capacity fee in proportion to use of the capacity of the wastewater system. The wastewater capacity fees set forth in this chapter shall be collected from new construction prior to issuance of a building permit, and for subdivisions prior to approval of a final map, unless other provisions are adopted as a part of an approved development agreement, or the City Council authorizes an alternative to the timing of such fees by resolution. (B) For the purposes of calculating the wastewater capacity fee, a single-family residence will be considered one \"equivalent dwelling unit (EDU),\" with one EDU being equal to a discharge of an average of three hundred gallons per day to the sanitary sewer. For the purposes of calculating the average daily discharge to the sanitary sewer for a multifamily residence, each multifamily residence unit will be assumed to be sixty-five percent of one single-family unit. (C) All applications for connection to the wastewater system by nonresidential connections will be required to pay a wastewater capacity fee proportional to the expected average daily discharge to the sewer system, as calculated by the applicant and certified by the city manager, public works director, or other designated staff. The applicant shall, using commonly accepted building and plumbing practices (such as the Uniform Plumbing Code) demonstrate the average daily discharge to the wastewater system, and the wastewater capacity fee will be calculated by multiplying this average daily discharge by the unit cost per gallons per day (gpd) according to the schedule below. (D) Wastewater capacity fees for all normal strength connections, as defined by Section 14.04.005 , shall be calculated based on the following schedule: Single-family residence (one EDU) $8,016.00 Multifamily residence (.65 EDU) $5,210.00 Commercial/industrial/public/other (per gpd) $26.72 ( Ord. No. 2024-07 ; Ord. 2007-12 \u00a7 1, 2007.) Cross References Section 14.06.030(A)", "num": "14.06.020", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06|14.06.020", "title": "14.06.020 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014All normal strength connections.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.06.030 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014High strength or industrial. (A) For all high strength connections to the wastewater system, the wastewater capacity fee shall be calculated based on the numbers of EDUs of the new connection, with each EDU paying the same rate as one EDU as outlined in Section 14.06.020(D) . EDUs = Average daily flow X [.448 + (.276 x BOD in mg/l) + (.276 x TSS in mg/l)] 300 gpd 236 mg/l 238 mg/l \"BOD\" means bio-chemical oxygen demand and \"TSS\" means total suspended solids. BOD and TSS are expressed in milligrams per liter (mg/l). Values of BOD and TSS for a particular project shall be subject to approval by the city engineer. The charges shall be subject to adjustment in accordance with Section 14.04.050(B) . (Ord. 2007-12 \u00a7 1, 2007.)", "num": "14.06.030", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06|14.06.030", "title": "14.06.030 Wastewater capacity fee\u2014High strength or industrial.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.06.040 Wastewater use substantially altered\u2014Additional wastewater capacity fee. If, in the judgment of the city manager or public works director, and after the final wastewater capacity fee is established, any customer increases the discharge to the wastewater system in a substantial and permanent way, due to changes in the size or nature of the building or premises previously permitted, the city shall charge and collect additional wastewater capacity charges based upon the increased use of wastewater capacity. The additional wastewater capacity fee shall be established by computing the new number of EDUs in service at the connection, and then subtracting from that figure the number of EDUs originally purchased in accordance with Section 14.08.020 or 14.08.030. (Ord. 2007-12 \u00a7 1, 2007.)", "num": "14.06.040", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06|14.06.040", "title": "14.06.040 Wastewater use substantially altered\u2014Additional wastewater capacity fee.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.06.050 Temporary wastewater connection fees. (A) The city council may adopt by resolution, temporary wastewater connection fees based on a finding by the city council that a particular use is temporary and does not conform to the typical use categories of residential, commercial or industrial. In such cases the temporary wastewater connection fee shall be charged for each unit of seven hundred forty-eight gallons of wastewater flow based on the following formula: Temporary Connection Fee = $3.29/unit of wastewater x (0.448 + (.276 x BOD (in mg/l) \u00f7 236) + (0.276 TSS (in mg/l) \u00f7 238)) (B) The city manager or his or her designee may be delegated responsibility for billing and monitoring temporary connection fees in accordance with this section . (Ord. 2007-12 \u00a7 1, 2007.)", "num": "14.06.050", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06|14.06.050", "title": "14.06.050 Temporary wastewater connection fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.06.060 Adjustments to wastewater connection fees. (A) The city at its sole discretion may adopt revised wastewater connection fees based on the proportionate effects of inflation or changes to the cost of living. The Engineering News Record Construction Cost Index for the San Francisco Area shall be used for adjusting wastewater connection fees. The adjustments in accordance with this section shall be made annually through 2011, thereafter adjustments to the connection/capacity fees shall be approved by a resolution of the city council. (B) The city council, at its sole discretion, may commit participation by the general fund of the city for fifty percent of the connection fee in an amount not to exceed ten thousand dollars to be applied to wastewater connection fees for a qualifying nonprofit or charitable organization in the city. (Ord. 2007-12 \u00a7 1, 2007.)", "num": "14.06.060", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06|14.06.060", "title": "14.06.060 Adjustments to wastewater connection fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 14.06.070 Reclaimed water mains. The city council may adopt by resolution a plan of reclaimed water mains to serve future growth of the city. New development which fronts such reclaimed water mains may be required to install such mains at no cost to the city. (Ord. 2007-12 \u00a7 1, 2007.)", "num": "14.06.070", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|14|1|14.06|14.06.070", "title": "14.06.070 Reclaimed water mains.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/14.06.070"}
