{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.010 Purpose. This chapter has been enacted for the purpose of establishing development impact fees to defray the actual costs of constructing traffic improvements to mitigate impacts resulting from proposed new development identified in the American Canyon general plan.", "num": "15.12.010", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.010", "title": "15.12.010 Purpose.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.020 Findings. (A) The American Canyon general plan land use element identifies projected build-out for the city of American Canyon; (B) Each new land development project in the city of American Canyon will generate additional traffic within the city limits of American Canyon, which will cumulatively cause adverse environmental effects if improvements for traffic circulation are not made; (C) The American Canyon general plan circulation element identifies the roadway and intersection improvements necessary to accommodate the anticipated levels of development; (D) Without a traffic mitigation fee, existing and future sources of revenue will be inadequate to fund a substantial portion of the improvements for traffic circulation which are necessary to avoid the unacceptable level of congestion and related adverse impacts created by expected development within the city of American Canyon; and (E) It is the intent of the city council to adopt by the ordinance codified in this chapter a fair and equitable method of securing the revenues necessary to fund the construction and implementation of necessary traffic circulation improvements. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999.)", "num": "15.12.020", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.020", "title": "15.12.020 Findings.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.030 Definitions. For the purposes of this chapter : (A) \"Construction\" means the original construction of a new single-family residence, townhouse, apartment, restaurant, motel or hotel, industrial use, retail use, office use, or institutional use. (B) \"Traffic improvements\" mean those roadway and intersection improvements identified in the Circulation Element of the General Plan, the current City Traffic Impact Mitigation Fee Nexus Study, and the City Capital Improvement Program. (C) \"Traffic mitigation fee\" or \"traffic impact fee\" or \"traffic development impact fee\" means that fee for traffic mitigation identified in the most recent traffic impact fee nexus study. (D) \"Traffic Impact Mitigation Fee Nexus Study\" or \"Traffic Development Impact Fee Study\" or \"Fee Study\" means the most recent study, adopted by resolution of the city council pursuant to Government Code Section 66000 et seq. (Mitigation Fee Act), of the nexus between traffic impact mitigation fees and traffic improvements needed to serve new development in American Canyon. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999; Ord. 2006-10 \u00a7 2, 2006; Ord. 2015-02 \u00a7\u00a7 1-3, 2015.)", "num": "15.12.030", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.030", "title": "15.12.030 Definitions.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.040 Exemptions. The following projects are exempt from the provisions of this chapter : (A) Development for which a vesting tentative map application has been accepted as complete or has been approved prior to the effective date of the amended ordinance codified in this chapter . In such cases, an agreed-upon fee as part of the conditions of approval for said application shall remain in effect; (B) Capital improvements/buildings related to the operation of the city of American Canyon governmental operations; (C) Temporary uses less than twelve months in duration; (D) Replacement development on a one-to-one basis for residential, industrial and commercial construction; (E) Replacement of commercial units destroyed by fire or natural disaster, provided the floor area is not increased. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999.)", "num": "15.12.040", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.040", "title": "15.12.040 Exemptions.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.050 Development impact fees. (A) A traffic impact fee is imposed on new construction as set forth in this chapter . The fee shall be in accordance with the most recent Traffic Impact Mitigation Fee Nexus Study. (B) The city at its sole discretion may adopt revised traffic mitigation impact fees based on the proportionate effects of inflation or changes to the cost of living. For purposes of calculation, the Engineering News Record 20-City Construction Cost Index shall be used for adjusting said fees. Said adjustments in accordance with this section may be approved by a resolution of the city council. (C) The city, at its sole discretion, may adopt revised traffic mitigation impact fees based on a revised Traffic Impact Mitigation Fee Nexus Study adopted by resolution of the City Council pursuant to the Mitigation Fee Act. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999; Ord. 2004-02 \u00a7 1, 2004; Ord. 2011-05 \u00a7 1, 2011; Ord. 2015-02 \u00a7\u00a7 4, 5, 2015.)", "num": "15.12.050", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.050", "title": "15.12.050 Development impact fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.060 Collection of fees. The development impact fees set forth in this chapter shall be collected from new construction prior to issuance of a building permit, and for subdivisions prior to approval of a final map, unless other provisions are adopted as a part of an approved development agreement, or the city council authorizes an alternative to the timing of such fees by resolution. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999; Ord. 2012-02 \u00a7 2, 2012.)", "num": "15.12.060", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.060", "title": "15.12.060 Collection of fees.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.070 In lieu contributions. The traffic impact fee set forth in this chapter may be reduced by a credit given for construction by a developer of all or a portion of the traffic improvement identified in this chapter subject to recommendation by the city engineer and approval by the city council. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999; Ord. 2015-02 \u00a7\u00a7 6, 7, 2015.)", "num": "15.12.070", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.070", "title": "15.12.070 In lieu contributions.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.090", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.090 Alternative commercial rate program. The alternative commercial rate program recognizes the diversity of commercial uses and the potential differences in traffic generation rates and peak hour characteristics. The city council may consider the findings of an independent traffic study, prepared under the direction of the city engineer and funded by the applicant, justifying a lesser traffic impact fee. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999; Ord. 2015-02 \u00a7 8, 2015.)", "num": "15.12.090", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.090", "title": "15.12.090 Alternative commercial rate program.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.090"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.100", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 15.12.100 Change of use. In the event of change of use in a development for which traffic impact fees were paid in accordance with this chapter , particularly those projects benefiting from either the special industrial incentive program or the alternative commercial rate program, the city council may require the payment of the difference between the traffic impact fees originally paid and the amount required by this chapter for new use. The community development director and city engineer shall forward a recommendation to the city council in each case. (Ord. 99-18 \u00a7 1, 1999.)", "num": "15.12.100", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|15|15.12|15.12.100", "title": "15.12.100 Change of use.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/15.12.100"}
