{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 19.53.010 Purpose and intent. The purpose and intent of this chapter is to establish ministerial zoning requirements for small-cell antenna facilities (SAFs) that improve high-speed wireless telecommunication services compatible with federal and state rules and regulations, provide cost recovery for impacts to the city infrastructure, and avoid potential adverse environmental impacts in the community such as noise, aesthetics, and public infrastructure maintenance. (Ord. 2018-05 \u00a7 8, 2018.)", "num": "19.53.010", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|19|3|19.53|19.53.010", "title": "19.53.010 Purpose and intent.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/19.53.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/19.53.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "City of American Canyon Municipal Code 19.53.020 Applicability. The provisions of this chapter apply to small-cell antenna facilities (SAFs) in the city of American Canyon. Small-cell wireless telecommunication facilities that do not comply with the SAF standards require a design permit approved by the planning commission in accordance with Chapter 19.41 . (Ord. 2018-05 \u00a7 8, 2018.)", "num": "19.53.020", "path": "library|City of American Canyon, Cal., Code|19|3|19.53|19.53.020", "title": "19.53.020 Applicability.", "url": "/us/ca/cities/american-canyon/code/19.53.020"}
